The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as semantic correspondence and image alignment, which are typically associated with the computer vision sub-category (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a novel neural network architecture for this task, which falls under the machine learning sub-category (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence sub-category (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of convolutional activations, which are commonly used in multimedia sub-category (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper discusses the use of weakly-supervised training, which is a common technique in neural network optimization and falls under the neural and evolutionary computing sub-category (cs.NE).
